==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|globus}}, {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|globe}} + {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|εἶδος||form, likeness}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|mathematics}} A [[spherical]] representation or [[projection]] of a [[sphere]] or [[ellipsoid]].
#: ''A '''globoid''' is always round.''
# Mathematical connotation of [[globe]].
#: ''Pictures of planets and moons are usually presented as '''globoids'''.''

